#: ../../../deprecations/pending-removal-in-future.rst:80
msgid ""
":mod:`os.path`: :func:`os.path.commonprefix` is deprecated, use :func:`os."
"path.commonpath` for path prefixes. The :func:`os.path.commonprefix` "
"function is being deprecated due to having a misleading name and module. The "
"function is not safe to use for path prefixes despite being included in a "
"module about path manipulation, meaning it is easy to accidentally introduce "
"path traversal vulnerabilities into Python programs by using this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../deprecations/pending-removal-in-future.rst:88
msgid ""
":class:`!pydoc.ErrorDuringImport`: A tuple value for *exc_info* parameter is "
